      • loadSchemaFromXmlResource

        public static Schema loadSchemaFromXmlResource(Class<?> resourceBaseClass,
                                               String resourceName)
                                        throws SchemaException,
                                               IOException
        Loads a schema from specified resource using default character encoding.
        Parameters:
        resourceBaseClass - A class that specifies the base for the relative location of the resource. If this parameter is null, the resource name has to specify the resource with an absolute path.
        resourceName - The name of the resource to load.
        Returns:
        A newly created schema from the supplied xml resource.
        Throws:
        SchemaException - When there is an error in the schema
        IOException - When there is an error reading from input

      • loadSchemaFromXmlResource

                                               String resourceName,
                                               String encoding)
                                        throws SchemaException,
                                               IOException
        Loads a schema from specified resource using supplied character encoding.
        Parameters:
        resourceBaseClass - A class that specifies the base for the relative location of the resource. If this parameter is null, the resource name has to specify the resource with an absolute path.
        resourceName - The name of the resource to load.
        encoding - The character encoding to use while reading resource.
        Returns:
        A newly created schema from the supplied xml resource.
        Throws:
        SchemaException - When there is an error in the schema
